Technical experts,
development agents,

00:19:03.250 --> 00:19:05.667
and production manuals were
deployed and distributed

00:19:05.834 --> 00:19:08.999
to various teff-growing areas,

00:19:08.999 --> 00:19:11.250
to facilitate and reinforce
the ATA's efforts.

00:19:11.417 --> 00:19:15.999
Though Ethiopia's teff
export policy allows

00:19:20.875 --> 00:19:23.999
for the export of
processed teff like flour,

00:19:23.999 --> 00:19:27.250
many people believe that
lifting the export ban

00:19:27.417 --> 00:19:29.999
on raw teff grains can
benefit the country greatly.

00:19:29.999 --> 00:19:33.999
Since demand for
teff is increasing,

00:19:33.999 --> 00:19:36.625
income from international trade

00:19:36.792 --> 00:19:38.792
and the export of raw
teff grains can contribute

00:19:38.959 --> 00:19:41.999
to the country's gross
domestic product or GDP

00:19:41.999 --> 00:19:45.625
and to Ethiopia's overall growth
and transformation plants.

00:19:45.792 --> 00:19:50.625
Lifting the export ban can
also introduce the small teff

00:19:52.667 --> 00:19:55.999
market to more modern
interventions, which can further

00:19:56.083 --> 00:19:59.999
improve productivity
to secure food security

00:19:59.999 --> 00:20:03.500
not just in Ethiopia
but in the whole world.

00:20:03.667 --> 00:20:07.999
Teff may be a 100%
Ethiopian grain,

00:20:19.792 --> 00:20:22.875
but that does not mean
that different cultures

00:20:22.999 --> 00:20:25.667
should not get the opportunity
to enjoy this grain's mixture

00:20:25.834 --> 00:20:29.250
of mild, nutty,
and sweet flavors.

00:20:29.417 --> 00:20:33.417
Teff's texture varies depending

00:20:35.417 --> 00:20:37.000
on the method
applied in cooking.

00:20:37.166 --> 00:20:39.625
For a poppyseed-like texture,
perfect for salads and stews,

00:20:39.792 --> 00:20:44.041
cook 1 cup of teff in 1 cup
of water for 6-7 minutes

00:20:44.208 --> 00:20:48.999
and let it stand covered for
5 minutes more before serving.

00:20:48.999 --> 00:20:53.999
For a creamier
texture like porridge,

00:20:55.999 --> 00:20:58.417
cook 1 cup of teff in 3 cups
of water for 20 minutes.

00:20:58.583 --> 00:21:03.417
Here's a recipe using
teff flour called

00:21:03.667 --> 00:21:06.875
Teff Crepe with
Spinach and Mushroom.

00:21:06.999 --> 00:21:09.625
For the crepe, you will
need 1/2 cup of teff flour,

00:21:09.792 --> 00:21:14.041
1/2 teaspoon of salt,
1/2 cup of whole milk,

00:21:14.208 --> 00:21:18.250
1 large egg and 1
tablespoon of melted butter.

00:21:18.417 --> 00:21:22.166
For the filling,

00:21:22.333 --> 00:21:23.750
you will need 1 tablespoon
of extra virgin olive oil,

00:21:23.917 --> 00:21:26.999
227 grams of sliced mushrooms,
6 cups of fresh baby spinach,

00:21:26.999 --> 00:21:31.999
salt, freshly ground black
pepper and parmesan cheese.

00:21:33.458 --> 00:21:38.291
First, make the filling.

00:21:38.999 --> 00:21:40.834
Heat oil in a large
nonstick skillet or pan

00:21:40.999 --> 00:21:43.999
over medium-high heat.

00:21:43.999 --> 00:21:46.250
Sauté mushrooms for 5 minutes,
then add spinach, salt,

00:21:46.417 --> 00:21:50.667
and pepper and cook
for another minute.

00:21:50.834 --> 00:21:53.458
Remove from the pan.

00:21:53.625 --> 00:21:55.834
Second, prepare the crepes.

00:21:55.999 --> 00:21:58.667
In a medium bowl, combine
teff flour and salt.

00:21:58.834 --> 00:22:02.250
Then whisk the milk, egg, and
melted butter in another bowl.

00:22:02.417 --> 00:22:06.999
Add the milk
mixture to the flour

00:22:06.999 --> 00:22:08.999
and whisk until
it becomes smooth.

00:22:09.125 --> 00:22:12.834
Using the same skillet or pan,

00:22:12.999 --> 00:22:15.250
pour a quarter cup
of the crepe batter

00:22:15.417 --> 00:22:18.834
and tilt it in a circular motion

00:22:18.999 --> 00:22:20.709
to spread the batter
thinly and evenly.

00:22:20.875 --> 00:22:23.999
Cook for 45 seconds.

00:22:23.999 --> 00:22:26.999
Then use a spatula to flip over

00:22:26.999 --> 00:22:29.542
and cook the other side
another 30 seconds.

00:22:29.709 --> 00:22:33.208
Repeat the same process until
all the batter is used up.

00:22:33.375 --> 00:22:37.959
Third, divide the
filling among the crepes.

00:22:39.625 --> 00:22:43.250
Roll them and sprinkle
parmesan cheese before serving.

00:22:43.417 --> 00:22:47.625
Teff flour is popularly
used in making injera.

00:22:47.792 --> 00:22:51.625
The traditional way
of making injera,

00:22:51.792 --> 00:22:53.999
usually takes 3-5 days due
to the fermentation process.

00:22:53.999 --> 00:22:58.208
Here is an injera recipe you
can finish in 1 1/2 days.

00:22:58.375 --> 00:23:02.250
Prepare the following, 1
1/2 cups of teff flour,

00:23:02.417 --> 00:23:07.250
2 cups of water, 1/2
teaspoon of baking powder,

00:23:07.417 --> 00:23:12.250
oil for the pan, 1/4
teaspoon of salt.

00:23:12.500 --> 00:23:16.667
First, ferment the
teff flour this way.

00:23:16.834 --> 00:23:19.625
Put the flour and
water in a large bowl.

00:23:19.792 --> 00:23:22.625
Stir well, cover with a towel,

00:23:22.792 --> 00:23:25.250
place somewhere where
it will not be disturbed

00:23:25.417 --> 00:23:27.834
and let it sit for 24 hours.

00:23:27.999 --> 00:23:30.834
After 24 hours, stir in
the salt and baking powder.

00:23:30.999 --> 00:23:35.041
The mixture will deflate
once you stir it.

00:23:35.208 --> 00:23:38.208
Now, it's time to cook.

00:23:38.375 --> 00:23:40.999
Heat and oil pan
over medium-heat.

00:23:41.083 --> 00:23:43.834
Pour the batter into the pan,

00:23:43.999 --> 00:23:45.458
enough to fill the surface
and cover with a lid.

00:23:45.625 --> 00:23:49.250
Keeping the moisture
is important

00:23:49.417 --> 00:23:51.250
to prevent the
injera from cracking.

00:23:51.417 --> 00:23:54.834
Cook for 5-7 minutes or
until the top becomes dry

00:23:54.999 --> 00:23:58.667
and the edges begin to curl.

00:23:58.834 --> 00:24:00.667
Remove from pan and
repeat the process

00:24:00.834 --> 00:24:02.999
until all the batter is used up.

00:24:02.999 --> 00:24:05.999
It is clear that teff has
more potential beyond injera

00:24:06.709 --> 00:24:10.999
and as a awareness for this
grain continues to rise,

00:24:10.999 --> 00:24:14.625
it will not be surprising
if the world gets to enjoy

00:24:14.792 --> 00:24:18.250
new and exciting teff-based
meals some time in the future.